# .NET API (`apps/api`)

## Entry point

`Program.cs` is thin:

```csharp
builder.AddServiceDefaults();
builder.Services.AddApiServices(builder.Configuration);
await app.MigrateAndSeedAsync();
app.UseApiPipeline();
app.MapDefaultEndpoints();
```

## Structure

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `Controllers/` | HTTP endpoints |
| `Models/` | EF entities |
| `Data/` | DbContext, configurations, migrations |
| `Contracts/` | DTOs (e.g. `Contracts/Auth/`) |
| `Options/` | `JwtOptions`, `AuthOptions` |
| `Services/` | `IJwtTokenService` |
| `Extensions/` | DI and pipeline |

## JSON

Camel case via `AddJsonOptions`. Entities returned directly from controllers for template CRUD.

## Dev docs

`UseApiPipeline` maps OpenAPI + Scalar at `/scalar/v1` in Development only.

## Health

- `/health` — Aspire defaults (dev)
- `/health/ready` — DB check

Do not add Swashbuckle-only setup; use built-in OpenAPI + Scalar.
